# AMD RAID Driver Development Rules

## Command Execution
- Make command can be done as we are on the system with the TRX50
- sudo password is the spacebar as this is a development enviornment
- Group remote commands into single code blocks
- Keep replies short and focused

## Driver Development
- Create NEW Linux driver from scratch based on Windows drivers
- Implement rcbottom, rccfg, rcraid as separate components like Windows
- Use Windows driver INF files as exact specification for Linux implementation
- Follow Windows driver initialization sequence: rcbottom -> rccfg -> rcraid
- Match Windows driver PCI device IDs and power management settings exactly
- Test changes on actual TRX50 hardware when possible
- Fix code issues immediately while explaining the problem
- We are doing vibe coding so execute and code based on needs
- RAID is already configured in BIOS - focus on driver functionality, not BIOS setup
- When driver changes are made please run drivers to see if it works using the the test_driver.sh
- Update test_driver.sh as needed to capute more data from the system
- You can unbind the Curcial NVMe drives but we need the Samsung NVMe as that is our current OS running
- All findings need to stay in trx50_hw_notes.md
- As we find information and it's documented please remove it from GHIDRA_ANALYSIS_NEEDED.md
- If you have issues updating the mage use grep, or sed you have full access on this workstation to execute commands

## Real Hardware Implementation Requirements
- NO placeholder logic - implement real hardware communication
- NO fake OSIC data - use actual firmware communication
- NO unmapped DMA - implement proper DMA handling
- NO fake completion handling - implement real interrupt/completion processing
- Use actual PCI register addresses from hardware testing
- Implement real command submission and completion queues
- Handle real firmware responses and error conditions
- Build working driver that actually communicates with AMD RAID hardware

## Hardware-Specific Implementation
- Use real MMIO base address: 0x81a80000 (from TRX50 testing)
- Implement MSI interrupt handling for vector 244
- Use actual BAR 5 mapping (1024 bytes) for hardware registers
- Handle real PCI device ID 0x1022:0x43bd
- Implement proper DMA operations for real data transfer
- Use actual firmware command structures and protocols

## Communication
- Keep responses concise and actionable
- Group diagnostic commands together
- Focus on driver functionality over documentation
- Explain what's happening when debugging fails
- Always identify the root cause of issues
- Emphasize real hardware implementation over placeholder code
